theorem closure_inter_interior_subset_closure_inter {X : Type*} [TopologicalSpace X]
    {A B : Set X} :
    closure A ∩ interior B ⊆ closure (A ∩ B) := by
  intro x hx
  rcases hx with ⟨hxClA, hxIntB⟩
  -- We will show that every open set containing `x` meets `A ∩ B`.
  have h_goal : x ∈ closure (A ∩ B) := by
    -- Use the neighborhood characterization of `closure`.
    refine (mem_closure_iff).2 ?_
    intro U hUopen hxU
    -- From `hxIntB`, obtain an open set `V` with `x ∈ V ⊆ B`.
    rcases (Set.mem_interior).1 hxIntB with ⟨V, hVopen, hVsubB, hxV⟩
    -- Consider the open set `W = U ∩ V` containing `x`.
    set W := U ∩ V with hWdef
    have hWopen : IsOpen W := hUopen.inter hVopen
    have hxW : x ∈ W := by
      have : x ∈ U ∩ V := And.intro hxU hxV
      simpa [hWdef] using this
    -- Because `x ∈ closure A`, `W` meets `A`.
    have hNon : (A ∩ W).Nonempty :=
      (mem_closure_iff).1 hxClA W hWopen hxW
    -- Extract a witness `y`.
    rcases hNon with ⟨y, hyA, hyW⟩
    have hyU : y ∈ U := by
      have : y ∈ W := hyW
      simpa [hWdef] using this.1
    have hyV : y ∈ V := by
      have : y ∈ W := hyW
      simpa [hWdef] using this.2
    have hyB : y ∈ B := hVsubB hyV
    -- `y` lies in `U ∩ (A ∩ B)`.
    exact ⟨y, hyU, And.intro hyA hyB⟩
  exact h_goal
